{"key":"post-10851364","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10851364</id>\n<content>Let us know how the vikur works out.&amp;nbsp; The main benefit of vermiculite is it holds a lot of water, like a mineral sponge.&amp;nbsp; Test the vikur to see if it holds water and if you can take a handful and squeeze the water out.&amp;nbsp; If not, it's probably a better substitute for perlite in your terrarium.&amp;nbsp; You can make brf cakes with coir instead of vermiculite, but they don't perform quite as well.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10851421</next>\n<prev>10851348</prev>\n<first>10850962</first>\n<last>10875477</last>\n<when>1250173048</when>\n<utime>08/13/09 05:17 PM</utime>\n</post>"}